Date: 1 Mar 2022
Source: Rising Sun [edited]
https://risingsunchatsworth.co.za/192236/sweets-leave-sour-taste-as-school-pupils-fall-ill-at-montford-school/


Pandemonium broke out as children from a local primary school were left ill after ingesting sweets, which allegedly contained drugs, last week.

Communications officer of Chatsworth SAPS, Cpt Cheryl Pillay, confirmed 11 children fell victim to these 'drug sweets', filling parents and teachers with panic.

"Chatsworth police are appealing to parents and pupils to be cautious while at school. Police have been to the school where pupils were cautioned on purchasing sweets from fellow schoolmates and strangers. We are advising parents to take precautions in this regard. Children must be aware of what drug sweets are and what these do to children. Should a child consume these sweets, it could result in serious health conditions with symptoms including nervousness, dry mouth, dilated pupils, and extreme energy followed by fatigue," explained Cpt Pillay.

If you notice your child is experiencing these symptoms, you should seek help immediately.

Chatsworth police will continue to monitor the pupils at school, however, a shared responsibility rests upon parents and teachers.

[Byline: Sarvasan Pillay]

